Senator Overcash
1 moves to amend the bill on page 2, lines 30 through 34, by rewriting the lines to read:
2
3 "(7b) Robocall. – A voice communication that delivers artificial, artificially
4 generated, or prerecorded voice messages, in whole or in part, including, but
5 not limited to, telephone calls utilizing soundboard technology and ringless
6 voicemail messages. "Robocall" also includes spam and scam text messages
7 received by a telephone subscriber through a messaging application. The
8 following are not considered a "robocall": (i) a voice communication made
9 with the prior express written consent of the telephone subscriber that delivers
10 artificial, artificially generated, or prerecorded voice messages, in whole or in
11 part, including, but not limited to, telephone calls utilizing soundboard
12 technology and ringless voicemail messages, and (ii) text messages sent with
13 the prior express written consent of the telephone subscriber received by a
14 telephone subscriber through a messaging application.".
